<html>
<body>
Reports method calls in EL that don't match <code>method-signature</code> constraints in TLD files.

<p><b>Example Java class:</b></p><br/>
<pre><code lang="java">
public class ExampleAction {
  public void goodAction() { ... }
  public void badAction(String str) { ... }
}
</code></pre>

<p><b>Example JSP file:</b></p><br/>
<pre><code lang="jsp">
&lt;jsp:useBean id="example" scope="request" type="org.example.ExampleAction"/&gt;
&lt;f:view&gt;
  &lt;h:commandButton action="#{example.goodAction}"/&gt; // Good: method accepts zero arguments and returns `void`
  &lt;h:commandButton action="#{example.badAction}"/&gt; // Error: method `void badAction(String)` returns `java.lang.String` type instead of `void`
&lt;/f:view&gt;
</code></pre>
</body>
</html>
